agentfs serve --help
Serve an AgentFS filesystem via different protocols

Usage: agentfs.exe serve <COMMAND>

Commands:
  nfs   Start an NFS server to export an AgentFS filesystem over the network
  mcp   Start an MCP server exposing filesystem and KV-store tools
  help  Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help  Print help

agentfs serve nfs --help
Start an NFS server to export an AgentFS filesystem over the network

Usage: agentfs.exe serve nfs [OPTIONS] <ID_OR_PATH>

Arguments:
  <ID_OR_PATH>  Agent ID or database path

Options:
      --bind <BIND>  IP address to bind to [default: 127.0.0.1]
      --port <PORT>  Port to listen on [default: 11111]
  -h, --help         Print help

agentfs nfs --help
Start an NFS server to export an AgentFS filesystem over the network (deprecated: use `agentfs serve nfs` instead)

Usage: agentfs.exe nfs [OPTIONS] <ID_OR_PATH>

Arguments:
  <ID_OR_PATH>  Agent ID or database path

Options:
      --bind <BIND>  IP address to bind to [default: 127.0.0.1]
      --port <PORT>  Port to listen on [default: 11111]
  -h, --help         Print help
